# 1. Project Overview

This portfolio documents my individual contribution to the CSC 308 team project
*"Exploratory Analysis of Spotify Audio Features Across Music Genres Using R."*
The team dataset was `genres_v2.csv` (Kaggle: mrmorj, 2020), sourced from the
Spotify Web API. The team produced six core visualizations — three distribution
histograms (danceability, energy, tempo), a scatter plot of energy vs. loudness,
a boxplot of danceability across the top 10 genres, and a correlation matrix of
all numeric audio features — and used them to answer four research questions
about feature distributions, energy-loudness coupling, genre-level danceability
differences, and pairwise feature correlations.

---

# 2. My Role on the Team

**Primary Role: Person 5 — Writing Lead**

My responsibilities focused on the written sections of the final paper that
required synthesizing the team's findings into clear, well-structured academic
writing. Specifically, I authored the following three sections:

1. **Section 1.2 — Problem Description:** Defining the research problem clearly,
   explaining why Spotify's audio features are worth studying, and establishing
   the real-world relevance of the analysis for recommendation systems, artists,
   and researchers.

2. **Section 6 — Limitations and Future Work:** Critically evaluating the
   boundaries of our study — including dataset bias, temporal limitations, and
