# 5. Supporting Code for Section 6 — Limitations and Future Work

The Limitations section makes specific claims about dataset bias, absent genres,
and feature redundancy. The code below is the verification I ran before writing
those claims so they were defensible.

## 5.1 Identifying Absent Genre Types

A core limitation I wrote about is that the dataset is missing entire categories
of music. I documented which genres were present versus what a truly balanced
music dataset would include.

```{r absent-genres}
present_genres <- sort(unique(spotify_df$genre))
cat("Genres present in our dataset:\n")
print(present_genres)

cat("\nGenre categories notably absent from the dataset:\n")
absent <- c("classical", "jazz", "folk", "gospel",
            "ambient", "blues", "country", "soul", "reggae")
cat(paste("-", absent, collapse = "\n"), "\n")

cat("\nThis absence was the primary dataset bias discussed in Section 6.\n")
```

## 5.2 Energy Skew — Quantifying the High-Intensity Bias

The Limitations section describes the dataset as skewed toward high-energy
music. I measured exactly how skewed it was so the claim was specific.

```{r energy-skew}
energy <- spotify_df$energy[!is.na(spotify_df$energy)]

cat("Mean energy:", round(mean(energy), 3), "\n")
cat("Median energy:", round(median(energy), 3), "\n")
cat("Tracks with energy above 0.75:",
    round(mean(energy > 0.75) * 100, 1), "%\n")
cat("Tracks with energy below 0.25:",
    round(mean(energy < 0.25) * 100, 1), "%\n")
cat("\nThis confirmed the dataset is heavily biased toward high-intensity tracks.\n")
```

## 5.3 Feature Independence — Backing the Future Work Recommendation

In Future Work I recommended removing redundant features before building
predictive models. I checked how many feature pairs were actually near-zero
in correlation to support this recommendation.

```{r feature-independence}
numeric_feats <- c("danceability", "energy", "loudness", "speechiness",
                   "acousticness", "instrumentalness", "liveness",
                   "valence", "tempo")

numeric_feats <- numeric_feats[numeric_feats %in% names(spotify_df)]
corr_mat <- cor(spotify_df[numeric_feats], use = "complete.obs")

corr_vals  <- corr_mat[lower.tri(corr_mat)]
n_weak     <- sum(abs(corr_vals) < 0.20)
n_total    <- length(corr_vals)

cat("Feature pairs with |r| < 0.20 (essentially independent):",
    n_weak, "out of", n_total, "\n")
cat("That is", round(n_weak / n_total * 100, 1),
    "% of all pairs — most features are independent.\n")
cat("The few redundant ones (energy-loudness) are candidates for removal in future models.\n")
```

