# 6. Supporting Code for Section 7 — Conclusion

The Conclusion addresses all four research questions directly. Before writing
each RQ response I verified the key numbers so the Conclusion was precise
and accurate.

## 6.1 RQ1 — Feature Distributions

```{r rq1-distributions}
dance <- spotify_df$danceability[!is.na(spotify_df$danceability)]
tempo <- spotify_df$tempo[!is.na(spotify_df$tempo)]

# Danceability modal bin
breaks     <- seq(0, 1, by = 0.01)
bin_counts <- table(cut(dance, breaks = breaks, include.lowest = TRUE))
top_bin    <- names(sort(bin_counts, decreasing = TRUE))[1]
cat("Danceability modal bin:", top_bin, "\n")

# Tempo bimodality
d       <- density(tempo, adjust = 1)
is_peak <- c(FALSE, diff(sign(diff(d$y))) < 0, FALSE)
peaks   <- data.frame(BPM     = round(d$x[is_peak], 1),
                      Density = round(d$y[is_peak], 6)) %>%
           arrange(desc(Density))

cat("\nTop tempo density peaks (confirms bimodal structure):\n")
print(head(peaks, 3))
```

## 6.2 RQ2 — Energy and Loudness Relationship

```{r rq2-energy-loudness}
r_el <- cor(spotify_df$energy, spotify_df$loudness,
            use = "complete.obs", method = "pearson")

cat("Pearson r (energy vs. loudness):", round(r_el, 3), "\n")
cat("Direction: positive — higher energy tracks tend to be louder.\n")
```

## 6.3 RQ3 — Genre Predicts Danceability

```{r rq3-genre-danceability}
dance_by_genre <- spotify_df %>%
  group_by(genre) %>%
  summarise(
    Median_Danceability = round(median(danceability, na.rm = TRUE), 3),
    N = n()
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(Median_Danceability))

kable(dance_by_genre,
      caption = "Median danceability by genre — verified before writing RQ3 response in Conclusion")
```

